OL,3,CSocial housing tenants 'coughing up
OL,4,Cblack phlegm' in mouldy home
OL,6,FA couple claims they are "coughing up
OL,7,Fblack phlegm" from living in a mouldy
OL,8,Fproperty run by the government social
OL,9,Fhousing provider Andium Homes.
OL,11,FLaura Richmond and Paul Hacquoil say
OL,12,Fthey have been staying in damp
OL,13,Fconditions at Brompton Villas in St
OL,14,FHelier for more than a year and it is
OL,15,Fcausing them endless stress.
OL,17,FThe pair add they are sleeping in
OL,18,Fcoats on their living room floor
OL,19,Fbecause the bedroom feels too cold.
